cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC, cs.CY, cs.SI 

The paper discusses the evaluation of computational models of explanation in Bayesian networks using human judgments. This involves both artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques for developing the models, as well as human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and cybersecurity (cs.CY) considerations for understanding the strengths and shortcomings of the models. Additionally, the paper touches on the social implications (cs.SI) of pursuing computational and psychological investigations of explanation in parallel.
